WEBVTT

00:01.520 --> 00:04.159
- Have any homework this weekend?
- A little.

00:04.320 --> 00:06.390
Why don't you
get started on it tonight.

00:06.560 --> 00:07.629
But it's only Friday.

00:07.800 --> 00:10.075
I know, but if you do it tonight,
you won't worry.

00:10.280 --> 00:11.554
I'm not worried.

00:14.800 --> 00:16.631
Hey. What are you guys up to tonight?

00:16.800 --> 00:19.189
- Jake's gonna do his homework.
- Why?

00:20.680 --> 00:23.148
It's only Friday.

00:24.640 --> 00:26.437
Let me tell you something
about Charlie.

00:26.600 --> 00:29.558
He was a lousy student. He always
put off doing his homework...

00:29.720 --> 00:33.474
...and his grades reflected it.
- Seems like he's doing okay now.

00:37.120 --> 00:39.793
- Go get your books.
- I left my books at Mom's.

00:39.960 --> 00:43.919
- Fine. I'll have her bring them over.
- Okay. They're in my bag.

00:45.280 --> 00:46.952
Go get them.

00:48.240 --> 00:50.151
Okay. Well, don't wait up.

00:51.000 --> 00:53.719
- Pretty confident, huh?
- Yeah.

00:53.880 --> 00:56.314
Thus, the "don't wait up."

00:56.480 --> 00:58.630
Didn't you meet this girl
a couple of days ago?

00:58.800 --> 01:02.110
Yup. So tonight's the night.
You know, the three-day rule.

01:02.280 --> 01:03.759
That's the three-date rule.

01:05.400 --> 01:06.958
Three dates? That's crazy talk.

01:08.200 --> 01:10.919
All right. If you bring her
back here, please be discreet.

01:11.080 --> 01:13.230
Don't worry.
First night's always at her place.

01:13.400 --> 01:16.870
- Is that another rule?
- No. It's just a common courtesy.

01:18.280 --> 01:21.192
A woman's more relaxed and
comfortable in her own surroundings.

01:22.360 --> 01:25.557
Plus, the minute she falls asleep,
I can hit the bricks.

01:25.720 --> 01:28.280
That's lovely. It's a shame
you don't work for Hallmark.

01:28.440 --> 01:31.591
Yeah, I'll bet those guys
get laid like crazy.

01:32.440 --> 01:34.431
- Goodnight, buddy.
- Night.

01:34.840 --> 01:36.478
What happened
to my chicken nuggets?

01:36.640 --> 01:38.471
What are you talking about?
You ate them.

01:38.640 --> 01:40.756
Now, stop procrastinating
and do your homework.

01:42.000 --> 01:43.513
What does procrastinating mean?

01:43.680 --> 01:46.319
It means putting off stuff
that you have to do.

01:47.960 --> 01:50.633
- Can you use it in a sentence?
- I just did.

01:51.200 --> 01:52.553
Oh, yeah.

01:53.960 --> 01:56.315
Did I tell you a bug
flew in my ear today?

02:00.520 --> 02:02.272
Charlie?

02:03.040 --> 02:06.828
- You asleep?
- What? No.

02:07.000 --> 02:09.594
No. You?

02:09.759 --> 02:12.399
Listen, I have to
get up early tomorrow, so...

02:12.800 --> 02:14.518
- You want me to leave?
- Do you mind?

02:14.680 --> 02:17.114
No, I'm cool either way:
Stay or go.

02:17.280 --> 02:18.918
Okay.

02:19.400 --> 02:20.992
So I'm going?

02:22.760 --> 02:24.034
Thanks, you're a doll.

02:27.720 --> 02:32.748
You know, I actually prefer
waking up in my own bed.

02:33.440 --> 02:35.192
Personal little quirk.

02:35.760 --> 02:38.149
- You don't mind, right?
- Not at all.

02:38.320 --> 02:40.231
Good.

02:40.400 --> 02:44.109
So this worked out well
for all concerned, huh?

02:44.280 --> 02:46.396
It was fantastic.
We'll have to do it again.

02:47.040 --> 02:48.632
Absolutely.

02:49.880 --> 02:53.475
- But not tonight?
- No.

02:54.880 --> 02:58.839
- Okay. Well, I'll call you.
- It's probably easier if I call you.

03:00.560 --> 03:01.834
Sure. Either way.

03:02.000 --> 03:04.036
- I call you, you call me.
- I'll call you.

03:05.800 --> 03:07.677
Good.

03:07.840 --> 03:10.593
- So I guess I'll just let myself out.
- Okay.

